We recommended that the Inventory Committee continue the physical count of all PPE items taking into consideration the prescribed procedural guidelines for inventory taking as provided in COA Circular No. 2020-006, to wit:

 Use the inventory working papers provided by the General Service Office (GSO) as basis for inventory taking activities, taking into consideration the capitalization threshold of P15,000.00;
 Record physical count in a standard Inventory Count Form (ICF), which shall be used as the basis in the preparation of the RPCPPE after the physical count;
 Tag all PPE items counted with new property stickers containing the information provided by the said Circular;
 State clearly in the ICF the PPEs’ condition, found at station and not found during the physical count which described as “non-existing” or “missing”, as well as other relevant information of each PPE; and
 Prepare the RPCPPE upon completion of the physical count.

We recommended that the Inventory Committee continue the physical count of all PPE items taking into consideration the prescribed procedural guidelines for inventory taking as provided in COA Circular No. 2020-006, to wit:

a.	Use the inventory working papers provided by the General Service Office (GSO) as basis for inventory taking activities, taking into consideration the capitalization threshold of P15,000.00;

b.	Record physical count in a standard Inventory Count Form (ICF), which shall be used as the basis in the preparation of the RPCPPE after the physical count;

c.	Tag all PPE items counted with new property stickers containing the information provided by the said Circular;

d.	State clearly in the ICF the PPEs’ condition, found at station and not found during the physical count which described as “non-existing” or “missing”, as well as other relevant information of each PPE; and

e.	Prepare the RPCPPE upon completion of the physical count.

In view of the foregoing, we recommended the following:

a.)	Submit written explanation/justification for the grant of discounts at varied amounts on selected taxpayers by tampering the duplicate official receipts and/or inaccurate computation of interest on RPT; 

b.)	Provide a copy of approved ordinance authorizing the grant of discount on delinquent RPT payments in conformity with applicable laws, rules and regulations. In absence thereof, immediately collect the under-collection of RPT totaling P 506,013.32 from the concerned taxpayers;

c.)	The Honorable Mayor shall direct the OIC-Municipal Treasurer to strictly impose the uniform application of two percent monthly interest rate on delinquent RPT payments in accordance with Section 255 of Republic Act 7160; and

d.)	The OIC- Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant shall revisit their internal control to strengthen the sound monitoring and control mechanism of the Municipality to address the identified issues.

